{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862471029,"sessionID":"ses_28659c8d1ffegZ2Rx2bb0HSP9i","part":{"id":"prt_d79a6d41a0012uO08Qr7K7A2ru","messageID":"msg_d79a6ae00001qNaAC1pHYnQh95","sessionID":"ses_28659c8d1ffegZ2Rx2bb0HSP9i","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-7c59745884634125b91426d99a6bf112","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Dependencies Setup\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1** Add gin dependency\n20:   - Run: `go get github.com/gin-gonic/gin@v1.10.0`\n21:   - Verify: `go mod tidy && cat go.mod | grep gin-gonic`\n22:   - Independently verifiable: `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` appears in go.mod\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2** Add jwt dependency\n25:   - Run: `go get github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5@v5.2.0`\n26:   - Verify: `go mod tidy && cat go.mod | grep golang-jwt`\n27:   - Independently verifiable: `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` appears in go.mod\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3** Create package directories\n30:   - Run: `mkdir -p pkg/picod cmd/picod`\n31:   - Verify: `ls pkg/picod cmd/picod`\n32:   - Independently verifiable: Both directories exist\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ### Phase 2: Config Struct\n37: \n38: - [ ] **T2.1** Create `pkg/picod/config.go` with Config struct\n39:   - Define `Config struct` with `Port int` and `Workspace string` fields\n40:   - Add doc comment describing PicoD configuration\n41:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n42:   - Independently verifiable: File compiles without error\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ### Phase 3: Server Struct and Constructor\n47: \n48: - [ ] **T3.1** Create `pkg/picod/server.go` with Server struct\n49:   - Define `Server struct` with fields:\n50:     - `config *Config`\n51:     - `engine *gin.Engine`\n52:     - `httpServer *http.Server`\n53:     - `authManager *AuthManager`\n54:     - `workspace string`\n55:     - `startTime time.Time`\n56:   - Add `readHeaderTimeout = 10 * time.Second` constant\n57:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n58:   - Independently verifiable: Struct compiles without AuthManager reference error\n59: \n60: - [ ] **T3.2** Implement `NewServer(config *Config) (*Server, error)`\n61:   - Initialize `engine` with `gin.New()`\n62:   - Set `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)`\n63:   - Apply `gin.Logger()` and `gin.Recovery()` middleware\n64:   - Resolve workspace: empty → `os.Getwd()`, relative → `filepath.Abs(workspace)`\n65:   - Initialize `authManager` via `NewAuthManager()`\n66:   - Set `startTime = time.Now()`\n67:   - Configure `http.Server` with Addr, Handler, ReadHeaderTimeout\n68:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n69:   - Independently verifiable: Constructor compiles\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T3.3** Implement `Run(ctx context.Context) error`\n72:   - Call `s.httpServer.ListenAndServe()`\n73:   - Log error via `klog.ErrorS(err, \"server error\")` on failure\n74:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n75:   - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n76: \n77: - [ ] **T3.4** Implement route registration in `NewServer`\n78:   - Register `/health` with `HealthCheckHandler` (no auth)\n79:   - Create `/api` group with `authManager.AuthMiddleware()`\n80:   - Register `/api/execute` POST → `ExecuteHandler`\n81:   - Register `/api/files` POST → `UploadFileHandler`\n82:   - Register `/api/files` GET → `ListFilesHandler`\n83:   - Register `/api/files/*path` GET → `DownloadFileHandler`\n84:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n85:   - Independently verifiable: Route registration compiles\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ### Phase 4: AuthManager and JWT Middleware\n90: \n91: - [ ] **T4.1** Create `pkg/picod/auth.go` with AuthManager struct\n92:   - Define `AuthManager struct` with `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey` and `mutex sync.RWMutex`\n93:   - Add constants: `PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`, `MaxBodySize = 32 << 20`\n94:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n95:   - Independently verifiable: Struct and constants compile\n96: \n97: - [ ] **T4.2** Implement `NewAuthManager() (*AuthManager, error)`\n98:   - Call `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()`\n99:   - Set `publicKey` from loaded key\n100:   - Return error if env var missing\n101:   - Return error if PEM decode fails\n102:   - Return error if PKIX parse fails\n103:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n104:   - Independently verifiable: Constructor compiles\n105: \n106: - [ ] **T4.3** Implement `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv() (*rsa.PublicKey, error)`\n107:   - Read `os.Getenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)`\n108:   - Decode PEM block via `pem.Decode([]byte(pemKey))`\n109:   - Verify PEM block type is `\"PUBLIC KEY\"` (PKIX format)\n110:   - Parse via `x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey(block.Bytes)`\n111:   - Type-assert to `*rsa.PublicKey`\n112:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n113:   - Independently verifiable: Function compiles\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T4.4** Implement `AuthMiddleware() gin.HandlerFunc`\n116:   - Extract `Authorization` header via `c.GetHeader(\"Authorization\")`\n117:   - Return 401 with `\"missing authorization header\"` if header missing\n118:   - Strip `\"Bearer \"` prefix\n119:   - Return 401 with `\"invalid token format\"` if prefix missing\n120:   - Parse JWT with options: `jwt.WithExpirationRequired()`, `jwt.WithIssuedAt()`, `jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)`\n121:   - Validate signing method: type-assert to `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`, reject non-RSA\n122:   - Return 401 with `\"invalid signing method\"` for non-RSA\n123:   - Verify signature with public key\n124:   - Return 401 with `\"invalid signature\"` for invalid signature\n125:   - Return 401 with `\"token is expired\"` for expired token\n126:   - Apply `http.MaxBytesReader(w, r.Body, MaxBodySize)` on success\n127:   - Call `c.Next()` on success\n128:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n129:   - Independently verifiable: Middleware compiles\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ### Phase 5: Path Sanitization\n134: \n135: - [ ] **T5.1** Create `pkg/picod/sanitize.go` with sanitizePath function\n136:   - Signature: `func sanitizePath(workspace, requestedPath string) (string, error)`\n137:   - Resolve workspace symlinks: `filepath.EvalSymlinks(workspace)`\n138:   - Clean requested path: `filepath.Clean(requestedPath)`\n139:   - Strip leading `/`: `strings.TrimPrefix(cleaned, \"/\")`\n140:   - Join with workspace: `filepath.Join(resolvedWorkspace, cleaned)`\n141:   - Check traversal: `filepath.Rel(workspace, candidate)`, error if starts with `..`\n142:   - Re-validate existing paths after symlink resolution\n143:   - Return sanitized absolute path\n144:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n145:   - Independently verifiable: Function compiles\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ### Phase 6: Execute Handler\n150: \n151: - [ ] **T6.1** Create `pkg/picod/execute.go` with structs\n152:   - Define `ExecuteRequest struct`:\n153:     - `Command []string` with `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`\n154:     - `Timeout string` with `json:\"timeout\"`\n155:     - `WorkingDir string` with `json:\"working_dir\"`\n156:     - `Env map[string]string` with `json:\"env\"`\n157:   - Define `ExecuteResponse struct`:\n158:     - `Stdout string`, `Stderr string`, `ExitCode int`\n159:     - `Duration float64`, `StartTime time.Time`, `EndTime time.Time`\n160:   - Add constants: `TimeoutExitCode = 124`, `defaultTimeout = 60 * time.Second`\n161:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n162:   - Independently verifiable: Structs and constants compile\n163: \n164: - [ ] **T6.2** Implement `ExecuteHandler(c *gin.Context)`\n165:   - Bind `ExecuteRequest` via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n166:   - Return 400 for binding failure\n167:   - Validate `len(req.Command) > 0`, return 400 with `\"missing command\"`\n168:   - Parse timeout via `time.ParseDuration(req.Timeout)`, use default on error\n169:   - Create context with deadline: `context.WithTimeout(c.Request.Context(), timeout)`\n170:   - Build command: `exec.CommandContext(ctx, req.Command[0], req.Command[1:]...)`\n171:   - Sanitize working directory via `sanitizePath`, return 400 on escape\n172:   - Set `cmd.Dir` to sanitized path or workspace\n173:   - Augment env: `cmd.Env = os.Environ()` + `req.Env` entries\n174:   - Capture stdout/stderr via `bytes.Buffer`\n175:   - Execute with timing: `startTime`, `endTime`, `cmd.Run()`\n176:   - Handle timeout: `ctx.Err() == context.DeadlineExceeded` → exitCode 124, stderr \"command timed out\"\n177:   - Handle exit error: `exec.ExitError.ExitCode()`\n178:   - Return 200 with `ExecuteResponse`\n179:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n180:   - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ### Phase 7: File Handlers\n185: \n186: - [ ] **T7.1** Create `pkg/picod/files.go` with structs\n187:   - Define `FileInfo struct`: `Path`, `Size`, `Mode`, `Modified`\n188:   - Define `UploadFileRequest struct`: `Path`, `Content` (Base64), `Mode`\n189:   - Define `FileEntry struct`: `Name`, `Size`, `Modified`, `Mode`, `IsDir`\n190:   - Define `ListFilesResponse struct`: `Files []FileEntry`, `Path string`\n191:   - Add constants: `maxFileMode = 0777`, `defaultFileMode = 0644`\n192:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n193:   - Independently verifiable: Structs and constants compile\n194: \n195: - [ ] **T7.2** Implement `parseFileMode(modeStr string) (os.FileMode, error)`\n196:   - Return `defaultFileMode` for empty string\n197:   - Parse via `strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)`\n198:   - Return `defaultFileMode` on parse error\n199:   - Return error `\"invalid file mode\"` if mode > `maxFileMode`\n200:   - Return `os.FileMode(mode)`\n201:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n202:   - Independently verifiable: Function compiles\n203: \n204: - [ ] **T7.3** Implement `UploadFileHandler(c *gin.Context)`\n205:   - Detect content type: `c.ContentType()`\n206:   - Multipart: extract `path` via `c.PostForm(\"path\")`, `file` via `c.FormFile(\"file\")`, `mode` via `c.PostForm(\"mode\")`\n207:   - Return 400 for missing path/file\n208:   - JSON: bind `UploadFileRequest`, decode Base64 via `base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString`\n209:   - Return 400 for invalid Base64\n210:   - Sanitize path via `sanitizePath`, return 400 on escape\n211:   - Parse mode via `parseFileMode`, return 400 if > 0777\n212:   - Create parent dirs: `os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(sanitizedPath), 0755)`\n213:   - Write file: `os.WriteFile(sanitizedPath, content, mode)`\n214:   - Return 200 with `FileInfo`\n215:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n216:   - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n217: \n218: - [ ] **T7.4** Implement `ListFilesHandler(c *gin.Context)`\n219:   - Extract path: `c.Query(\"path\")`\n220:   - Return 400 with `\"missing path parameter\"` if empty\n221:   - Sanitize path via `sanitizePath`, return 400 on escape\n222:   - Read directory: `os.ReadDir(sanitizedPath)`\n223:   - Return 500 with `\"failed to read directory\"` on error\n224:   - Build `FileEntry` for each entry, skip failed `Info()`\n225:   - Format mode: `fmt.Sprintf(\"%04o\", info.Mode().Perm())`\n226:   - Return 200 with `ListFilesResponse`\n227:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n228:   - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n229: \n230: - [ ] **T7.5** Implement `DownloadFileHandler(c *gin.Context)`\n231:   - Extract path: `c.Param(\"path\")`\n232:   - Strip leading `/`: `strings.TrimPrefix(path, \"/\")`\n233:   - Sanitize path via `sanitizePath`, return 400 on escape\n234:   - Check existence: `os.Stat(sanitizedPath)`\n235:   - Return 404 with `\"file not found\"` if not exists\n236:   - Return 400 with `\"path is not a file\"` if directory\n237:   - Detect Content-Type: `mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(sanitizedPath))`\n238:   - Set `Content-Disposition`: `attachment; filename=\"<filename>\"`\n239:   - Stream file: `c.File(sanitizedPath)`\n240:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n241:   - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ### Phase 8: Health Handler\n246: \n247: - [ ] **T8.1** Create `pkg/picod/health.go`\n248:   - Define constants: `version = \"0.0.1\"`, `service = \"PicoD\"`\n249:   - Implement `HealthCheckHandler(c *gin.Context)`\n250:   - Return 200 with JSON: `status=\"ok\"`, `service`, `version`, `uptime=time.Since(startTime).String()`\n251:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n252:   - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n253: \n254: ---\n255: \n256: ### Phase 9: Entry Point\n257: \n258: - [ ] **T9.1** Create `cmd/picod/main.go`\n259:   - Set klog stderr: `flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")`\n260:   - Init klog flags: `klog.InitFlags(nil)`\n261:   - Define `-port` flag with default 8080\n262:   - Define `-workspace` flag with default empty\n263:   - Parse flags: `flag.Parse()`\n264:   - Create `Config` from flag values\n265:   - Call `NewServer(config)`, `klog.Fatalf` on error\n266:   - Call `server.Run(context.Background())`\n267:   - Log startup: `klog.InfoS(\"PicoD started\", \"port\", port, \"workspace\", workspace)`\n268:   - Verify: `go build ./cmd/picod/`\n269:   - Independently verifiable: Binary builds successfully\n270: \n271: ---\n272: \n273: ### Phase 10: Unit Tests\n274: \n275: - [ ] **T10.1** Create `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` with test helpers\n276:   - Implement `setupTestServer(t *testing.T) *Server`\n277:   - Create temp workspace via `t.TempDir()`\n278:   - Generate RSA key pair for test JWT signing\n279:   - Set `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var with PEM public key\n280:   - Create `Server` with test workspace\n281:   - Independently verifiable: Test helper compiles\n282: \n283: - [ ] **T10.2** Test `sanitizePath` scenarios\n284:   - Valid relative path: returns absolute path within workspace\n285:   - Absolute path: strips leading `/`, resolves within workspace\n286:   - Path traversal `../escape`: returns error\n287:   - Deep traversal `subdir/../../escape`: returns error\n288:   - Null byte: cleaned safely\n289:   - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n290: \n291: - [ ] **T10.3** Test `AuthMiddleware` scenarios\n292:   - Missing Authorization: HTTP 401, `\"missing authorization header\"`\n293:   - Invalid format: HTTP 401\n294:   - Expired token: HTTP 401, `\"token is expired\"`\n295:   - HS256 token: HTTP 401, `\"invalid signing method\"`\n296:   - Valid RS256 token: request proceeds\n297:   - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n298: \n299: - [ ] **T10.4** Test `ExecuteHandler` scenarios\n300:   - Valid command `echo hello`: stdout=\"hello\\n\", exit_code=0\n301:   - Empty command: HTTP 400\n302:   - Timeout exceeded: exit_code=124, stderr=\"command timed out\"\n303:   - Invalid timeout string: uses default 60s\n304:   - Working directory: stdout shows subdir path\n305:   - Path escape working_dir: HTTP 400\n306:   - Environment augmentation: stdout contains MY_VAR\n307:   - Exit code propagation: exit_code=42 for `exit 42`\n308:   - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n309: \n310: - [ ] **T10.5** Test `UploadFileHandler` scenarios\n311:   - Multipart upload: HTTP 200, FileInfo returned\n312:   - JSON Base64 upload: HTTP 200, FileInfo returned\n313:   - Invalid Base64: HTTP 400\n314:   - Path escape: HTTP 400\n315:   - Invalid mode: uses default 0644\n316:   - Mode > 0777: HTTP 400\n317:   - Parent directory creation: parents created with 0755\n318:   - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n319: \n320: - [ ] **T10.6** Test `ListFilesHandler` scenarios\n321:   - Valid directory: HTTP 200, FileEntry array\n322:   - Missing path: HTTP 400\n323:   - Path escape: HTTP 400\n324:   - Non-existent directory: HTTP 500\n325:   - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n326: \n327: - [ ] **T10.7** Test `DownloadFileHandler` scenarios\n328:   - Existing file: HTTP 200, file content\n329:   - Leading slash stripped: resolved correctly\n330:   - Path escape: HTTP 400\n331:   - File not found: HTTP 404\n332:   - Path is directory: HTTP 400, `\"path is not a file\"`\n333:   - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n334: \n335: - [ ] **T10.8** Test `HealthCheckHandler`\n336:   - No JWT required: HTTP 200\n337:   - Response contains status=\"ok\", service=\"PicoD\", version=\"0.0.1\"\n338:   - Uptime is duration string\n339:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n340: \n341: - [ ] **T10.9** Test `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` scenarios\n342:   - Missing env var: error\n343:   - Invalid PEM: error\n344:   - PKCS#1 format: not supported, error\n345:   - Valid PKIX PEM: returns RSA public key\n346:   - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n347: \n348: ---\n349: \n350: ### Phase 11: Validation and Integration\n351: \n352: - [ ] **T11.1** Run `go vet ./pkg/picod/... ./cmd/picod/...`\n353:   - Verify: No warnings\n354:   - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n355: \n356: - [ ] **T11.2** Run `golangci-lint run ./pkg/picod/... ./cmd/picod/...`\n357:   - Verify: No errors\n358:   - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n359: \n360: - [ ] **T11.3** Run all tests with race detector\n361:   - Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/... -race -v`\n362:   - Independently verifiable: All tests pass\n363: \n364: - [ ] **T11.4** Verify test coverage ≥ 80%\n365:   - Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out`\n366:   - Run: `go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep total`\n367:   - Independently verifiable: Coverage ≥ 80%\n368: \n369: - [ ] **T11.5** Run binary with test public key\n370:   - Generate RSA key pair\n371:   - Set `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var\n372:   - Run: `./picod -port=8080 -workspace=/tmp/test`\n373:   - Call `/health`: verify 200 response\n374:   - Independently verifiable: Server starts and responds\n375: \n376: ---\n377: \n378: ## Acceptance Criteria\n379: \n380: - [ ] All 8 source files created in `pkg/picod/`\n381: - [ ] Entry point `cmd/picod/main.go` created\n382: - [ ] Config struct with Port and Workspace fields\n383: - [ ] Server struct with Gin engine, AuthManager, workspace, startTime\n384: - [ ] JWT RS256 authentication with 5 error cases\n385: - [ ] Execute handler with timeout, working_dir, env support\n386: - [ ] File upload handler supporting multipart and JSON/Base64\n387: - [ ] File list and download handlers with path sanitization\n388: - [ ] Health check handler (no auth required)\n389: - [ ] sanitizePath with workspace jail enforcement\n390: - [ ] Pass `go vet`\n391: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint`\n392: - [ ] Test coverage ≥ 80%\n393: - [ ] Binary runs with JWT auth and executes commands\n394: \n395: ---\n396: \n397: ## File Changes Summary\n398: \n399: | File | Action | Lines Changed |\n400: |------|--------|---------------|\n401: | `go.mod` | Modify | +2 (gin, jwt dependencies) |\n402: | `pkg/picod/config.go` | Create | ~15 lines |\n403: | `pkg/picod/server.go` | Create | ~80 lines |\n404: | `pkg/picod/auth.go` | Create | ~100 lines |\n405: | `pkg/picod/execute.go` | Create | ~100 lines |\n406: | `pkg/picod/files.go` | Create | ~150 lines |\n407: | `pkg/picod/health.go` | Create | ~20 lines |\n408: | `pkg/picod/sanitize.go` | Create | ~50 lines |\n409: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | Create | ~40 lines |\n410: | `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Create | ~200 lines |\n411: \n412: ---\n413: \n414: ## Implementation Notes\n415: \n416: - Gin framework: `gin.New()` for engine, `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)` for production\n417: - JWT validation: use `jwt.WithExpirationRequired()`, `jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)`\n418: - RSA signing: type-assert `token.Method` to `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`\n419: - Path sanitization: `filepath.EvalSymlinks()` for symlink resolution, `filepath.Rel()` for traversal check\n420: - Command execution: `exec.CommandContext()` for timeout enforcement, exit code 124 for timeout\n421: - Base64 decoding: `base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString()` for JSON file upload\n422: - File mode parsing: `strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)` for octal parsing\n\n(End of file - total 422 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Dependencies Setup\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Add gin dependency\n  - Run: `go get github.com/gin-gonic/gin@v1.10.0`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775862471014,"end":1775862471027}}}}
