{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862570468,"sessionID":"ses_28659c8d1ffegZ2Rx2bb0HSP9i","part":{"id":"prt_d79a85d7c001utn8ieekQX4fgJ","messageID":"msg_d79a71e3c001WhFwdgD6sKf32Z","sessionID":"ses_28659c8d1ffegZ2Rx2bb0HSP9i","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-7b3b13b8f9504bd5a425cccf1a4b6c24","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/tasks.md","content":"# AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Implementation Verification\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Verify `pkg/picod/files.go` structs exist\n  - Check: `FileInfo`, `UploadFileRequest`, `FileEntry`, `ListFilesResponse`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Structs compile without error\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Verify `parseFileMode` function exists\n  - Check: Function handles empty, invalid, valid, and >0777 modes\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Function compiles\n\n- [ ] **T1.3** Verify `UploadFileHandler` exists\n  - Check: Handler supports multipart and JSON/Base64 upload\n  - Check: Handler validates path, Base64, mode, creates parent dirs\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n\n- [ ] **T1.4** Verify `ListFilesHandler` exists\n  - Check: Handler validates path, reads directory, builds FileEntry array\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n\n- [ ] **T1.5** Verify `DownloadFileHandler` exists\n  - Check: Handler strips leading slash, validates path, detects MIME type\n  - Check: Handler sets Content-Disposition header, streams file\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n\n- [ ] **T1.6** Verify route registration in `pkg/picod/server.go`\n  - Check: `/api/files` POST → UploadFileHandler\n  - Check: `/api/files` GET → ListFilesHandler\n  - Check: `/api/files/*path` GET → DownloadFileHandler\n  - Verify: `grep -n \"api.*files\" pkg/picod/server.go`\n  - Independently verifiable: All three routes registered\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: File Upload Handler Tests\n\n- [ ] **T2.1** Test multipart upload\n  - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerMultipart` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerMultipart ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, file written\n\n- [ ] **T2.2** Test JSON Base64 upload\n  - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerJSON` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerJSON ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, content decoded\n\n- [ ] **T2.3** Test invalid Base64 content\n  - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidBase64` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidBase64 ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid base64 content\"\n\n- [ ] **T2.4** Test path traversal detection\n  - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerPathEscape` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerPathEscape ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid path\"\n\n- [ ] **T2.5** Test invalid file mode (non-octal)\n  - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidMode` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidMode ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, uses default 0644\n\n- [ ] **T2.6** Test file mode > 0777\n  - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerModeTooHigh` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerModeTooHigh ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid file mode\"\n\n- [ ] **T2.7** Test parent directory creation\n  - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerParentDirectoryCreation` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerParentDirectoryCreation ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, parents created with 0755\n\n- [ ] **T2.8** Add test for multipart missing path\n  - Create: `TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingPath`\n  - Input: multipart form without `path` field\n  - Expected: HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\"\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingPath ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T2.9** Add test for multipart missing file\n  - Create: `TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingFile`\n  - Input: multipart form without `file` field\n  - Expected: HTTP 400, \"missing file\"\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingFile ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: File List Handler Tests\n\n- [ ] **T3.1** Test valid directory listing\n  - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerValidDirectory` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerValidDirectory ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, FileEntry array\n\n- [ ] **T3.2** Test missing path parameter\n  - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerMissingPath` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerMissingPath ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\"\n\n- [ ] **T3.3** Test path traversal detection\n  - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerPathEscape` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerPathEscape ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid path\"\n\n- [ ] **T3.4** Test non-existent directory\n  - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerNonExistent` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerNonExistent ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: HTTP 500, \"failed to read directory\"\n\n- [ ] **T3.5** Add test for empty directory\n  - Create: `TestListFilesHandlerEmptyDirectory`\n  - Setup: Create empty directory in workspace\n  - Expected: HTTP 200,