TestDownloadFileHandlerMIMETypeUnknown ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T4.8** Add test for symlink inside workspace\n  - Create: `TestDownloadFileHandlerSymlinkInsideWorkspace`\n  - Setup: Create file, create symlink pointing to file within workspace\n  - Expected: HTTP 200, file content from symlink\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerSymlinkInsideWorkspace ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n---\n\n### Phase 5: File Mode Parsing Tests\n\n- [ ] **T5.1** Test empty mode returns default\n  - Test: `TestParseFileModeEmpty` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeEmpty ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Returns 0644\n\n- [ ] **T5.2** Test invalid mode returns default\n  - Test: `TestParseFileModeInvalid` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeInvalid ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Returns 0644\n\n- [ ] **T5.3** Test mode > 0777 returns error\n  - Test: `TestParseFileModeTooHigh` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeTooHigh ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Returns error \"invalid file mode\"\n\n- [ ] **T5.4** Test valid mode parsing\n  - Test: `TestParseFileModeValid` exists and passes\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeValid ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Returns correct FileMode\n\n---\n\n### Phase 6: Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **T6.1** Test full file lifecycle\n  - Create: `TestFileLifecycle`\n  - Steps: Upload file → List directory → Download file → Verify content\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestFileLifecycle ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: All operations succeed, content matches\n\n- [ ] **T6.2** Test large file upload (near 32 MiB limit)\n  - Create: `TestUploadLargeFile`\n  - Setup: Generate file ~30 MiB\n  - Expected: HTTP 200, file written\n  - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadLargeFile ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T6.3** Test concurrent operations\n  - Create: `TestConcurrentFileOperations`\n  - Setup: Multiple upload/download requests in parallel\n  - Expected: All succeed without race conditions\n  - Verify: `go test -race -run TestConcurrentFileOperations ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes with race detector\n\n---\n\n### Phase 7: Validation and Linting\n\n- [ ] **T7.1** Run `go vet` on picod package\n  - Run: `go vet ./pkg/picod/... ./cmd/picod/...`\n  - Verify: No warnings\n  - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n\n- [ ] **T7.2** Run `golangci-lint` on picod package\n  - Run: `golangci-lint run ./pkg/picod/... ./cmd/picod/...`\n  - Verify: No errors\n  - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n\n- [ ] **T7.3** Run all tests with race detector\n  - Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/... -race -v`\n  - Verify: All tests pass\n  - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n\n- [ ] **T7.4** Verify test coverage ≥ 80%\n  - Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out`\n  - Run: `go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep total`\n  - Independently verifiable: Coverage ≥ 80%\n\n---\n\n### Phase 8: Binary Validation\n\n- [ ] **T8.1** Build picod binary\n  - Run: `go build -o picod ./cmd/picod/`\n  - Verify: Binary exists\n  - Independently verifiable: `ls picod`\n\n- [ ] **T8.2** Run binary with test public key\n  - Setup: Generate RSA key pair\n  - Setup: Set `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var\n  - Run: `./picod -port=8080 -workspace=/tmp/test`\n  - Call: `/health` endpoint\n  - Expected: HTTP 200 response\n  - Independently verifiable: Server starts and responds\n\n- [ ] **T8.3** Test file upload via binary\n  - Setup: Server running with valid JWT\n  - Call: `POST /api/files` with JSON upload\n  - Expected: HTTP 200, FileInfo returned\n  - Independently verifiable: File created in workspace\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `pkg/picod/files.go` contains FileInfo, UploadFileRequest, FileEntry, ListFilesResponse structs\n- [ ] `parseFileMode` handles empty/invalid/valid/>0777 modes correctly\n- [ ] `UploadFileHandler` supports multipart and JSON/Base64 upload\n- [ ] `UploadFileHandler` validates path, Base64, mode, creates parent directories\n- [ ] `ListFilesHandler` validates path, reads directory, returns FileEntry array\n- [ ] `DownloadFileHandler` validates path, detects MIME type, streams file\n- [ ] All three file routes registered in server.go\n- [ ] All file handler tests pass\n- [ ] Path traversal protection works for upload, list, download\n- [ ] File mode validation prevents setuid/setgid bits (max 0777)\n- [ ] Pass `go vet`\n- [ ] Pass `golangci-lint`\n- [ ] Test coverage ≥ 80%\n- [ ] Binary runs with JWT auth and handles file operations\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Lines Changed |\n|------|--------|---------------|\n| `pkg/picod/files.go` | Existing | ~230 lines |\n| `pkg/picod/server.go` | Existing | Routes at lines 71-73 |\n| `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Modify | +~60 lines (new tests) |\n| `cmd/picod/main.go` | Existing | ~35 lines |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- File upload supports both `multipart/form-data` and `application/json` (Base64 encoded)\n- Path sanitization via `sanitizePath` enforces workspace jail security\n- File mode parsing: `strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)` for octal, max 0777\n- MIME type detection: `mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(path))`\n- Content-Disposition header: `attachment; filename=\"<filename>\"`\n- Parent directories created with 0755 mode\n- Default file mode: 0644"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/picod/main.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/files.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/server.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchm